-- Poland's Cyfrowy owners agree $2 bln share swap to buy Polkomtel
-- By Adrian Krajewski
-- Thu Jan 16, 2014 09:28AM EST
-- None



WARSAW, Jan 16 (Reuters) - Shareholders at Poland's largest media group Cyfrowy Polsat <CPS.WA> on Thursday agreed to a 6.15-billion zloty ($2 billion) share issue to buy the country's No.3 mobile operator Polkomtel [PTL.UL] in a share swap deal.

